A C O N C U R R E N T R E S O L U T I O N
To recognize the impact of the lifeguard shortage in Ohio 1
and encourage individuals to consider a career as a 2
lifeguard. 3
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO (THE SENATE CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, Lifeguards working at beaches, swimming pools, and 4
water parks are responsible for preventing and responding to 5
emergencies and protecting countless individuals from death or 6
serious injury; and 7
WHEREAS, To become a lifeguard, an individual must undergo 8
training on water and land rescue techniques in a variety of 9
environments and how to deliver first aid and critical care to 10
injured individuals; and 11
WHEREAS, Closures of beaches, pools, and water parks and 12
work restrictions put in place in response to the COVID-19 13
pandemic prevented individuals from receiving the necessary 14
training to become a lifeguard, resulting in a shortage of 15
available lifeguards across the United States; and 16
WHEREAS, One-third of the 309,000 public pools in the 17
United States are being forced to close or reduce their hours of 18

