operations due to a lack of available lifeguards to staff the 19
pools; and 20
WHEREAS, The shortage of lifeguards at public pools has 21
resulted in reduced class offerings and safety training courses, 22
including community swimming lessons and water safety and 23
lifeguard recertification; and 24
WHEREAS, Many cities are unable to hire enough staff to 25
provide lifeguards for municipal beaches, leaving swimmers and 26
other beach-goers without access to trained staff in the event 27
of an emergency; and 28
WHEREAS, Cities in Ohio have been increasing the wages paid 29
to attract individuals to fill open lifeguard positions, 30
allowing a lifeguard in Ohio to earn an average wage of $18 per 31
hour, which is projected to increase 12% over the next five 32
years; and 33
WHEREAS, Numerous other benefits are available to 34
individuals who choose to seek a career as a lifeguard, 35
including paid training, retention bonuses, and flexible 36
scheduling; now therefore be it 37
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the 136th General 38
Assembly of the State of Ohio, in adopting this resolution, 39
recognize the impact of the lifeguard shortage in Ohio and 40
encourage individuals to consider a career as a lifeguard; and 41
be it further 42
RESOLVED, That the Clerk of the House of Representatives 43
transmit duly authenticated copies of this resolution to the 44
Governor of Ohio and the news media of Ohio. 45

